Detailed Description

A struct used to store information about responses in the cache's volatile memory.

About entry locking: An entry is locked using both a mutex and a counter. The counter keeps track of how many clients are accessing a given entry while the mutex provides a guarantee that updates to the counter are MT-safe. In addition, the HTTPCache object maintains a map which binds the FILE* returned to a client with a given entry. This way the client can tell the HTTPCache object that it is done with FILE *response and the class can arrange to update the lock counter and mutex.
